# Architecture Alignment (marketing v2)

## Layering

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
|-------|----------|----------------|
| Routes | `src/app/**/page.tsx` | `metadata`, compose sections, minimal logic |
| Domain UI | `src/components/marketing/{sections,pricing,blog,solutions,phones}/` | Page-specific presentation |
| Primitives | `src/components/marketing/primitives/` | `PageShell`, `MarketingSection`, headers, CTAs, FAQ |
| Content | `src/content/**` | Copy, FAQ data, pricing tables, blog posts |
| Lib | `src/lib/**` | Pure helpers (blog, typography, constants, search) |
| Shell | `src/components/layout/` | Nav, footer |
| shadcn | `src/components/ui/` | Base UI only |

## Required boundaries

- Route files must not embed long copy blocks — use `src/content/` or section components.
- Do not duplicate section padding (`py-*` on routes) — use `MarketingSection` / `PageShell`.
- Do not hardcode app or card origins — use `@/lib/constants` and CTA primitives.
- New major logic belongs in `src/lib/` until API slices are introduced.

## Future APIs

When `src/app/api/**` appears, add thin route handlers and delegate to modules under a dedicated folder (for example `src/server/` or slice-style `src/slices/`). Activate `marketing-api-future.mdc`.

## Verification

- Run typecheck, lint, build before merge.
- See `testing-strategy.mdc` for risk-based expectations.
